WEBVTT

00:06.615 --> 00:09.487
- I thought I made it clear
you weren't

00:09.531 --> 00:11.054
needed here anymore.
- Yeah, we got a missing child.

00:11.098 --> 00:12.751
I'm not going home
until we find him.

00:12.795 --> 00:15.058
- Tell me who you are!
- Julian, stop!

00:15.102 --> 00:17.191
- I'm your mom!
I'm your mother!

00:17.234 --> 00:18.627
I'm your mom.

00:18.670 --> 00:20.585
- You know who's driving
that van, don't you?

00:20.629 --> 00:23.762
- Harry, saving my son
isn't gonna save you.

00:23.806 --> 00:26.765
- This is all that Marin left
at The Grey Daughters.

00:26.809 --> 00:29.507
I know where she's going.
- You're never gonna show me

00:29.551 --> 00:31.335
what the work actually is,
are you?

00:31.379 --> 00:33.337
- You've already been
doing it.

00:33.381 --> 00:35.078
- It's me.

00:37.863 --> 00:40.301
- When do you stop
being guilty?

00:40.344 --> 00:43.130
When is it over?

00:43.173 --> 00:44.609
- I'm not sure.

00:56.708 --> 01:03.759
♪

01:22.125 --> 01:25.389
♪

01:27.609 --> 01:30.090
♪

01:31.787 --> 01:38.837
♪

02:23.317 --> 02:25.319
- Hey.

02:26.798 --> 02:29.279
Looks like there was
only one eyewitness.

02:29.323 --> 02:33.283
and he saw a man outside,
talking to Marin.

02:34.893 --> 02:36.721
- He was not certain,
but he did say

02:36.765 --> 02:38.854
he didn't see any sign
of Julian.

02:38.897 --> 02:41.509
- Could have been Vera's guy--
the one with the ponytail.

02:41.552 --> 02:44.207
- Thing is,
the medical examiner, he--

02:44.251 --> 02:45.687
he's saying that
it looks likely

02:45.730 --> 02:47.297
that it was an accident.

02:47.341 --> 02:49.778
The gun was in Marin's hand.

02:51.867 --> 02:53.477
- The burn wounds
and the contusions,

02:53.521 --> 02:55.827
an unusual entry wound--
and he's saying

02:55.871 --> 02:58.308
that it's likely
there was a struggle.

03:01.920 --> 03:03.705
- That explains the 911 call

03:03.748 --> 03:05.489
from inside the room.

03:05.533 --> 03:06.838
- Maybe.

03:06.882 --> 03:08.666
I wanna look around
one more time.

03:10.451 --> 03:13.193
- It's Brick.

03:13.236 --> 03:16.326
I'm gonna put you
on speakerphone with Ambrose.

03:17.284 --> 03:19.851
- Looks like something
was found in the commune raid:

03:19.895 --> 03:21.679
Payments to Mosswood.

03:21.723 --> 03:24.334
One grand via wire
twice a month.

03:24.378 --> 03:25.814
Thought you should know.

03:25.857 --> 03:29.252
- "Daedalus Shipping LLC,"

03:29.296 --> 03:30.340
whatever that is.

03:30.384 --> 03:32.429
All I got so far is a PO box.

03:32.473 --> 03:34.649
- Well, we ought to find out
who that is and if there's been

03:34.692 --> 03:37.391
any recent activity
on the account.

03:37.434 --> 03:39.219
- Will do.
- Detective Ambrose,

03:39.262 --> 03:40.829
we got a hit
on that brown Volvo

03:40.872 --> 03:42.396
that you mentioned.

03:44.615 --> 03:46.574
- Yeah.

03:46.617 --> 03:53.668
♪

04:06.855 --> 04:08.726
- They're just sitting
out there.

04:10.859 --> 04:13.383
- We were in pursuit
10, 12 miles.

04:13.427 --> 04:16.299
Cut them off here.
Got troopers on the other side.

04:16.343 --> 04:17.779
♪

04:17.822 --> 04:19.737
- They might be armed.

04:19.781 --> 04:21.609
ESU is on the way.

04:21.652 --> 04:23.306
- Let me take a look.

04:23.350 --> 04:24.960
All right.

04:25.003 --> 04:30.444
♪

04:31.923 --> 04:33.925
- We tried making contact.

04:33.969 --> 04:35.927
They're not responding.

04:35.971 --> 04:39.583
♪

04:39.627 --> 04:40.932
- I'm going in.

04:40.976 --> 04:43.413
- We need to hold for tactical.

04:43.457 --> 04:45.328
- There's a kid in the car.

04:45.372 --> 04:47.678
- Detective.
- Harry.

04:47.722 --> 04:49.941
♪

04:49.985 --> 04:52.292
Harry!

04:54.076 --> 05:01.301
♪

05:11.572 --> 05:13.748
Get out of the car.

05:13.791 --> 05:16.359
♪

05:16.403 --> 05:18.622
Get out of the car.

05:18.666 --> 05:25.673
♪

05:27.109 --> 05:29.372
Put your hands on the wheel.

05:29.416 --> 05:31.026
♪

05:31.069 --> 05:33.115
Get out.

05:33.158 --> 05:35.073
Get out.

05:35.117 --> 05:38.468
♪

05:38.512 --> 05:39.904
Take him.

05:39.948 --> 05:46.737
♪

05:46.781 --> 05:48.826
Where is he?

05:48.870 --> 05:50.828
Where the fuck is he?

05:50.872 --> 05:54.615
♪

05:54.658 --> 05:56.051
Sick!

05:56.094 --> 05:58.488
- He's just a decoy.

06:01.535 --> 06:08.542
♪

06:13.895 --> 06:18.943
♪

06:20.858 --> 06:22.904
♪

06:22.947 --> 06:24.862
[woman shouting
in foreign language]

06:24.906 --> 06:28.823
♪

06:30.651 --> 06:31.695
♪

06:31.739 --> 06:33.741
- Come on.

06:33.784 --> 06:35.656
Stay close.

06:35.699 --> 06:42.750
♪

06:43.794 --> 06:44.969
- No.

06:45.013 --> 06:46.710
- Good.

06:46.754 --> 06:48.103
Better if you just
stay put here until you leave.

06:48.146 --> 06:49.887
- Okay.

06:49.931 --> 06:52.586
- I think the, uh,
Pittsburg leg fell through.

06:52.629 --> 06:54.414
Alan got spooked.

06:59.027 --> 07:01.029
- He's not calling back.

07:02.509 --> 07:03.988
- Well, I don't think a bus
out of Port Authority

07:04.032 --> 07:06.077
was a great call, anyway.

07:06.121 --> 07:08.515
Too exposed.
- Maybe one of the overnights

07:08.558 --> 07:09.646
out of Chinatown
would be better.

07:09.690 --> 07:11.953
- Yeah, that's a good idea.

07:14.956 --> 07:17.480
- You wanna tell me
what's going on?

07:18.525 --> 07:21.441
- It's better for both of us
if I don't.

07:23.747 --> 07:25.575
- The authorities
in Bingham County

07:25.619 --> 07:27.098
have him in custody, now.
That's why we need a warrant.

07:27.142 --> 07:28.883
- Why do we even care
about this guy?

07:28.926 --> 07:30.841
- He's a Mosswood member
and we believe

07:30.885 --> 07:32.495
he was involved in the murder.
- But you don't have anything

07:32.539 --> 07:33.801
tying him to the crime scene.
- We might,

07:33.844 --> 07:35.629
if we could question him.
- Novack.

07:35.672 --> 07:37.761
You've had a long,
shitty night.

07:37.805 --> 07:39.633
This is all getting
way too personal.

07:39.676 --> 07:41.765
I should have taken you off
this case two days ago.

07:41.809 --> 07:44.072
Look, I want you to go home
and get some sleep.

07:44.115 --> 07:45.769
- Sir, all we need
is to ask Hutchinson...

07:45.813 --> 07:47.771
- It's an order.
I'm serious.

07:47.815 --> 07:49.860
Go home.

07:52.950 --> 07:55.736
And you--I'll let you know
if I need back-up.

07:59.000 --> 08:00.915
- Can I talk to you
for a second?

08:05.876 --> 08:07.922
I was hoping it didn't matter,
but I'm kind of

08:07.965 --> 08:09.140
bugging out right now.

08:11.055 --> 08:12.927
- Those Daedalus papers
that I called you about

08:12.970 --> 08:14.058
early this morning?

08:14.102 --> 08:16.234
I got them from Lidell's desk.

08:16.278 --> 08:17.584
I was looking
for some paperwork.

08:17.627 --> 08:19.150
I found 'em in his drawer.

08:19.194 --> 08:21.065
- And he didn't say anything
about it

08:21.109 --> 08:23.067
after the commune raid.
- No.

08:23.111 --> 08:25.635
Why would he sit on info
like that?

08:25.679 --> 08:27.637
He can't be with Mosswood.

08:27.681 --> 08:29.813
Doesn't make any sense.

08:33.687 --> 08:36.820
♪

08:44.436 --> 08:46.308
[soulful country music playing
over radio]

08:46.351 --> 08:48.702
- Maybe she'll finally find
some peace.

08:48.745 --> 08:52.836
♪

08:52.880 --> 08:54.708
- Maybe.

08:54.751 --> 08:56.231
♪

08:58.625 --> 09:00.191
♪

09:00.235 --> 09:02.716
- All roads lead to Mosswood.

09:02.759 --> 09:04.631
- Well...

09:04.674 --> 09:05.849
♪

09:05.893 --> 09:08.548
I'm just really grateful
you're here.

09:08.591 --> 09:11.594
♪

09:11.638 --> 09:13.814
This whole thing has...

09:13.857 --> 09:15.380
♪

09:15.424 --> 09:18.166
made me realize
just how lucky I am.

09:18.209 --> 09:19.733
♪

09:19.776 --> 09:21.735
I don't know
what I'd do without you.

09:21.778 --> 09:23.693
I really don't.

09:23.737 --> 09:24.868
- Dad...

09:24.912 --> 09:26.609
- I know...

09:26.653 --> 09:28.742
I haven't been great at...

09:28.785 --> 09:31.179
talking about things.

09:31.222 --> 09:33.311
♪

09:33.355 --> 09:36.358
I know how--how hard
that's made things for you.

09:36.401 --> 09:41.624
♪

09:41.668 --> 09:43.887
- I'm sorry that I've been
so difficult.

09:43.931 --> 09:45.759
- No, no, no.

09:45.802 --> 09:48.370
Why don't you crash here
tonight?

09:48.413 --> 09:50.764
Get something to eat
and have a bath.

09:50.807 --> 09:53.505
Get out of that
stinky uniform.

09:55.507 --> 09:59.337
♪

10:08.172 --> 10:15.223
♪

10:22.970 --> 10:25.668
- Do not--don't!

10:27.322 --> 10:28.279
Don't--don't!

10:30.542 --> 10:35.809
♪

10:38.855 --> 10:45.906
♪

10:56.264 --> 10:59.528
woman: 911, what is
your emergency?

10:59.571 --> 11:02.618
Hello?
Is anyone there?

11:02.662 --> 11:09.669
♪

11:33.301 --> 11:34.345
- I'm fine.

11:41.831 --> 11:44.965
- I know we need to talk more
about what happened last night.

11:46.923 --> 11:50.013
You know you can ask me
anything.

11:56.367 --> 11:59.327
I'm sorry I lied to you
about Marin.

11:59.370 --> 12:00.763
I know
I only made things worse.

12:00.807 --> 12:03.461
I really was trying
to protect you.

12:11.992 --> 12:14.472
- What happens when we get
to Pittsburgh?

12:16.605 --> 12:17.998
- Some friends of mine
are gonna pick us up

12:18.041 --> 12:19.956
and drive us all the way
to Washington, to that place

12:20.000 --> 12:22.916
I was telling you about.

12:22.959 --> 12:24.744
We'll be surrounded by
the biggest trees

12:24.787 --> 12:26.876
you've ever seen.

12:50.334 --> 12:52.946
- Detective, I'm starting
to lose my patience, here.

12:52.989 --> 12:56.384
- I'd rather not do this
in the bullpen.

12:57.080 --> 13:00.605
It's not gonna look good
in front of your department.

13:04.044 --> 13:06.307
- Daedalus Shipping.

13:06.350 --> 13:08.439
It's a shell company
that's been making

13:08.483 --> 13:10.659
regular payments to Mosswood
for years, now.

13:10.702 --> 13:13.053
You know anything about that?

13:15.446 --> 13:17.666
- Every month, withdrawals
from the account

13:17.709 --> 13:19.320
have been automatic.

13:19.363 --> 13:21.322
We just figured out that
there was a cash withdrawal

13:21.365 --> 13:23.803
of almost three grand
that closed it out.

13:24.891 --> 13:26.849
Yesterday.

13:26.893 --> 13:29.765
Hours before the murder
last night.

13:30.810 --> 13:33.116
- You've been going through
my desk?

13:34.030 --> 13:35.684
- I think the important thing

13:35.727 --> 13:38.469
is why you've been sitting
on information

13:38.513 --> 13:40.515
that's crucial to the case.

13:40.558 --> 13:42.386
- You think I'm the guy
behind this?

13:42.430 --> 13:44.736
- Or you know who is.

13:57.445 --> 14:00.665
I had to be sure myself, first.

14:00.709 --> 14:02.842
Before anyone else.

14:05.888 --> 14:08.717
♪

14:19.206 --> 14:26.430
♪

14:34.221 --> 14:41.445
♪

14:53.631 --> 14:55.938
- Cool and cloudy,
with a high of 59.

14:55.982 --> 14:57.679
Light winds coming out
of the northeast,

14:57.722 --> 15:00.116
reasonable chance of light
rain in the evening,

15:00.160 --> 15:03.032
when we have a low of 56.

15:03.076 --> 15:05.034
Overnight rain will
increase...

15:05.078 --> 15:12.128
♪

15:20.310 --> 15:24.097
♪

15:25.228 --> 15:27.578
Why are you asking me that?

15:27.622 --> 15:29.319
- We just want to know
where you were

15:29.363 --> 15:31.452
two nights ago.

15:31.495 --> 15:33.671
- I was home.

15:33.715 --> 15:35.673
Made dinner and went to bed.

15:46.641 --> 15:48.948
- Found this in the dryer
last night.

15:51.428 --> 15:53.953
It fell out
of your pants pocket.

16:02.135 --> 16:05.138
- So you weren't home
that night.

16:07.009 --> 16:09.011
- Marin called me.

16:09.055 --> 16:11.274
She needed money,

16:11.318 --> 16:13.755
and I thought
if anyone deserved

16:13.798 --> 16:15.452
a fresh start, she did.

16:15.496 --> 16:18.107
So I drove up.

16:26.028 --> 16:28.683
- I can't do this
with Heather here.

16:36.778 --> 16:38.736
Dad.

16:40.260 --> 16:42.001
- I can't.

16:45.047 --> 16:52.054
♪

17:08.723 --> 17:11.160
- I got up there...

17:11.204 --> 17:13.423
and Marin was not...

17:13.467 --> 17:15.164
stable.

17:15.208 --> 17:17.514
I mean, the whole thing--
taking the boy

17:17.558 --> 17:20.039
and going to Canada.

17:20.082 --> 17:23.520
I told her, I said I wouldn't
let her do it.

17:23.564 --> 17:25.783
It's too crazy.

17:25.827 --> 17:27.394
♪

17:27.437 --> 17:29.526
Then she pulled a gun on me.

17:29.570 --> 17:31.093
♪

17:31.137 --> 17:32.529
I panicked.

17:32.573 --> 17:35.663
And I grabbed her hand...

17:35.706 --> 17:38.057
and the gun went off.

17:38.100 --> 17:41.538
♪

17:41.582 --> 17:44.106
I didn't kill her.

17:44.150 --> 17:47.370
♪

17:49.894 --> 17:51.461
♪

17:51.505 --> 17:54.116
- She knew I'd help her.

17:54.160 --> 17:55.422
♪

17:55.465 --> 17:57.685
You saw him?

17:57.728 --> 17:59.165
♪

17:59.208 --> 18:02.124
- I found him inside the cabin.

18:04.735 --> 18:06.476
- I brought him to Vera Walker.

18:06.520 --> 18:09.131
She took him.

18:09.175 --> 18:11.655
- You know Vera Walker.

18:11.699 --> 18:14.745
♪

18:16.834 --> 18:18.271
♪

18:18.314 --> 18:19.750
- Jack.

18:19.794 --> 18:21.752
♪

18:25.452 --> 18:28.107
Isn't this enough?

18:28.150 --> 18:35.157
♪

18:36.593 --> 18:38.595
- Daedalus.

18:38.639 --> 18:40.510
This is the company
you created

18:40.554 --> 18:44.166
so you could pay Vera
every month...

18:44.210 --> 18:46.603
for more than ten years.

18:46.647 --> 18:49.780
♪

18:49.824 --> 18:52.174
She has something on you.

18:52.218 --> 18:53.610
♪

18:53.654 --> 18:55.699
So, what is it?

18:55.743 --> 18:57.136
♪

18:57.179 --> 18:58.876
- All right.

18:58.920 --> 19:00.704
Here we go.
Come on, now.

19:00.748 --> 19:03.229
Help me.

19:03.272 --> 19:05.187
- Watch this move.

19:05.231 --> 19:07.276
Boom.

19:07.320 --> 19:08.625
Marin...
- Okay.

19:08.669 --> 19:11.193
Come on, let's go.

19:17.765 --> 19:19.201
- She hates me.

19:19.245 --> 19:21.595
- No, she doesn't.

19:25.425 --> 19:26.600
All right.

19:26.643 --> 19:28.254
Good night, kid.

19:28.297 --> 19:30.256
Get some sleep.
- I ruined it!

19:41.919 --> 19:43.965
- That's enough.

19:44.008 --> 19:46.228
- Oh, please.

19:46.272 --> 19:47.925
You could use one yourself.

19:47.969 --> 19:50.232
- What the hell happened
tonight?

19:50.276 --> 19:52.582
What'd you do to her?

19:52.626 --> 19:54.236
I didn't do anything.

19:54.280 --> 19:56.499
- She doesn't drink like that,
ever.

19:56.543 --> 19:58.458
- It's not my fault.
- Yeah, well, she's up there

19:58.501 --> 20:00.634
right now, crying and saying
that you hate her.

20:00.677 --> 20:04.377
so I'm of mind
it probably is your fault.

20:04.420 --> 20:06.248
- You're just like my mom.

20:06.292 --> 20:08.294
- I know you well enough,
Marin.

20:08.337 --> 20:09.991
I know how you can be.
- She thinks I hate her

20:10.034 --> 20:13.386
because I don't want
to have sex with her.

20:13.429 --> 20:15.388
Okay?

20:16.954 --> 20:19.566
Don't pretend like
you didn't know.

20:21.263 --> 20:23.700
- No.

20:23.744 --> 20:25.267
I knew.

20:25.311 --> 20:28.401
- And you never bothered
to talk to her about it?

20:30.054 --> 20:33.536
- I was respecting
her privacy.

20:33.580 --> 20:36.757
- You have any clue
how hard it is for her here?

20:38.019 --> 20:39.890
You just...

20:39.934 --> 20:43.720
make fucking pancakes
and hope for the best.

20:43.764 --> 20:45.853
That's a great plan.

20:50.814 --> 20:52.816
Whatever.

20:54.601 --> 20:55.863
- Marin.

20:55.906 --> 20:57.908
No, no, no.

20:57.952 --> 21:00.389
You are not going anywhere
tonight.

21:00.433 --> 21:01.999
- No, Marin.

21:02.043 --> 21:03.653
I mean it, now.

21:03.697 --> 21:05.394
Look, I'll drive you home,
or you can spend the night

21:05.438 --> 21:07.527
on the couch,
but you are not

21:07.570 --> 21:09.398
walking out of here tonight.

21:09.442 --> 21:12.271
You worried about me?

21:13.315 --> 21:15.317
- Yeah.

21:19.669 --> 21:22.281
- Whatever you say.

21:26.459 --> 21:28.765
- I'll get some sheets.

21:31.812 --> 21:38.862
♪

22:30.044 --> 22:32.655
Really?

22:34.875 --> 22:41.882
♪

22:45.059 --> 22:46.016
- Jack.

22:46.060 --> 22:48.105
♪

22:48.149 --> 22:50.760
- Jack...

22:50.804 --> 22:53.110
I think I should go.

22:55.112 --> 22:57.419
♪

22:59.465 --> 23:06.515
♪

23:16.786 --> 23:23.837
♪

23:30.757 --> 23:32.889
- Marin...

23:32.933 --> 23:35.544
Marin.

23:35.588 --> 23:42.595
♪

23:58.132 --> 24:00.743
Julian's my son.

24:08.577 --> 24:15.628
♪

24:27.727 --> 24:29.990
I can't go out there, Harry.

24:30.033 --> 24:32.688
♪

24:32.732 --> 24:35.125
I can't look at her.

24:35.169 --> 24:37.737
♪

24:37.780 --> 24:40.130
What am I gonna do?

24:40.174 --> 24:47.181
♪

25:07.288 --> 25:09.551
- Let's go.

25:19.605 --> 25:21.607
- I just saw the news.

25:21.650 --> 25:23.434
The Five Nations Motel?

25:23.478 --> 25:25.001
That girl is dead.

25:25.045 --> 25:27.221
- We had nothing
to do with that.

25:27.264 --> 25:29.658
- Then--then why
are they looking for you?

25:29.702 --> 25:32.182
- The police don't really know
what happened.

25:32.226 --> 25:33.662
♪

25:33.706 --> 25:35.577
- You know, I'm sorry.
You guys need to leave.

25:35.621 --> 25:37.231
I'm serious.

25:37.274 --> 25:38.798
This is too much.
- Fine.

25:38.841 --> 25:40.364
Two hours.
- That's all I need.

25:40.408 --> 25:41.801
I need to do something.
We'll come back,

25:41.844 --> 25:43.454
and we'll get out...
- And then you're gone.

25:43.498 --> 25:45.718
- I understand.
- What about transport

25:45.761 --> 25:47.676
to train stations,
bus stations?

25:47.720 --> 25:49.548
- We'll get the alert out.
- We're gonna need

25:49.591 --> 25:50.766
more help than that.

25:52.376 --> 25:53.334
I'll get in touch
with Border Patrol

25:53.377 --> 25:54.814
and the FBI.

25:54.857 --> 25:55.815
- Great.

25:55.858 --> 25:58.252
Excuse me.

25:58.295 --> 26:00.559
Hello?

26:00.602 --> 26:01.734
- It's Julian.

26:07.391 --> 26:08.436
You okay?

26:11.395 --> 26:12.701
- Yeah.

26:14.529 --> 26:16.096
- I can't tell you that.

26:18.228 --> 26:19.490
- Yeah, I am.

26:19.534 --> 26:21.797
Is she

26:21.841 --> 26:23.625
- If she doesn't bring you back

26:23.669 --> 26:25.235
she will be.

26:27.194 --> 26:28.630
- She has a plan for us
to go away

26:28.674 --> 26:30.458
and start over somewhere else.

26:31.677 --> 26:33.374
- Yeah, I figured.

26:33.417 --> 26:35.724
How do you feel about that?

26:37.421 --> 26:39.467
- I don't know.

26:41.774 --> 26:45.255
I tried to picture it but I--
I can't really picture it.

26:51.653 --> 26:54.308
- You don't have to go,
you know.

26:56.484 --> 26:59.269
- She's already
arranged everything.

26:59.313 --> 27:00.619
♪

27:00.662 --> 27:03.665
- It's not just up to her.

27:03.709 --> 27:05.841
The whole thing's about you,

27:05.885 --> 27:08.539
and you can choose
which way it goes.

27:08.583 --> 27:12.456
♪

27:14.720 --> 27:19.768
♪

27:19.812 --> 27:22.815
- I don't know.

27:22.858 --> 27:25.469
Depends on what
you can live with.

27:25.513 --> 27:31.171
♪

27:31.214 --> 27:32.476
- Oh, I'm sorry, I have to go.

27:32.520 --> 27:33.564
- Julian--

27:36.742 --> 27:38.352
- Come on, we've gotta go
pick something up.

27:42.573 --> 27:43.531
- Hey.

27:43.574 --> 27:45.533
I need a trace on this.

27:45.576 --> 27:48.667
Looks like he's in
New York City.

27:54.237 --> 28:01.288
♪

28:04.378 --> 28:06.380
- You have to leave us alone.

28:06.423 --> 28:08.512
- Marin, just come back.

28:08.556 --> 28:09.818
I'm on your side.

28:09.862 --> 28:11.341
I know Julian's your son.

28:11.385 --> 28:13.692
I know...

28:13.735 --> 28:15.694
what you've been through.

28:15.737 --> 28:18.827
♪

28:18.871 --> 28:20.829
- No, you don't.

28:20.873 --> 28:27.880
♪

28:30.796 --> 28:33.712
♪

28:35.757 --> 28:38.412
♪

28:47.813 --> 28:50.598
- Harry told me everything.

28:59.259 --> 29:01.957
I always knew something
happened that night.

29:04.917 --> 29:07.484
I could feel it.

29:10.879 --> 29:12.925
- I'm so sorry.

29:15.971 --> 29:17.451
Why?

29:19.801 --> 29:20.976
Why?

29:24.284 --> 29:26.460
Why'd you do it?

29:33.380 --> 29:35.774
Say something.

29:41.344 --> 29:43.303
Say something.

29:58.361 --> 30:05.412
♪

30:08.502 --> 30:12.854
♪

30:14.900 --> 30:19.905
♪

30:19.948 --> 30:21.863
- Let's go.

30:21.907 --> 30:24.953
♪

30:27.347 --> 30:29.828
♪

30:29.871 --> 30:31.655
No, thank you.

30:31.699 --> 30:38.097
♪

30:40.012 --> 30:41.491
Don't look.

30:42.884 --> 30:44.799
Don't look.

30:44.843 --> 30:51.806
♪

30:51.850 --> 30:53.677
Ten more minutes.
Then we'll go.

30:53.721 --> 30:56.942
I don't want to risk
waiting too long on the bus.

30:58.900 --> 31:00.859
- We can't go back
to Danielle's apartment.

31:00.902 --> 31:04.558
We'll pick up a few new things
once we get to Chicago.

31:15.438 --> 31:18.006
- I don't want to go
on the bus.

31:21.575 --> 31:23.925
- I don't want to go.

31:25.057 --> 31:27.624
I want to go back to Keller.

31:28.974 --> 31:32.020
- Honey, we passed that point.

31:32.064 --> 31:33.761
Things will be worse
if we go back now.

31:33.804 --> 31:35.894
We can't.

31:36.851 --> 31:39.375
- If we just keep running...

31:39.419 --> 31:41.595
it'll never stop.
- That's not true.

31:41.638 --> 31:43.466
I told you, we'll be safe
in Washington.

31:43.510 --> 31:44.554
We have friends there.

31:44.598 --> 31:46.861
We'll be able to start over.

31:51.997 --> 31:54.695
You just need some time.

31:55.609 --> 31:58.090
You'll feel better about it--
about all of it.

31:58.133 --> 32:00.614
I promise.

32:03.008 --> 32:05.445
- I want to go back.

32:09.928 --> 32:12.060
- We don't know what they're
gonna do to you there.

32:12.104 --> 32:14.584
They'll put you in jail.

32:14.628 --> 32:16.151
Or--or in a home.

32:17.761 --> 32:19.938
- I know.

32:21.896 --> 32:24.812
- They won't let me be
your mother.

32:27.162 --> 32:28.207
- I know.

32:33.690 --> 32:40.741
♪

32:42.656 --> 32:45.006
- So you've been thinking
about this for a while.

32:45.050 --> 32:46.747
♪

32:46.790 --> 32:47.878
- Yeah.

32:48.836 --> 32:53.014
♪

32:56.148 --> 32:57.627
Back to the apartment--

32:57.671 --> 32:59.890
back to the police.

32:59.934 --> 33:06.985
♪

33:10.858 --> 33:13.078
This is crazy.

33:13.121 --> 33:17.821
♪

33:17.865 --> 33:20.563
They might not let me
see you anymore.

33:20.607 --> 33:23.871
♪

33:23.914 --> 33:27.222
What if they don't
let me see you?

33:27.266 --> 33:29.920
- I'll tell them that I want
to see you and--

33:29.964 --> 33:31.922
and when I'm 18, I can see you

33:31.966 --> 33:34.142
whenever I want.

33:34.186 --> 33:41.193
♪

33:51.899 --> 33:58.949
♪

34:01.169 --> 34:04.216
- No.
Shh.

34:04.259 --> 34:06.522
- Shh.

34:06.566 --> 34:09.177
♪

34:09.221 --> 34:11.092
- Okay.

34:11.136 --> 34:18.186
♪

34:19.187 --> 34:20.754
Okay.

34:29.241 --> 34:31.678
- Brickowski.

34:46.214 --> 34:48.303
- Hi.

34:49.174 --> 34:51.089
- Hey.

34:53.308 --> 34:55.658
Glad you're back.

35:03.188 --> 35:05.015
We need you to stay

35:05.059 --> 35:07.192
and answer some questions.

35:09.194 --> 35:11.979
- Whatever you need.

35:12.022 --> 35:14.851
- I don't want my mother
to get in trouble.

35:27.386 --> 35:30.084
- So that is dandelion root.
- Mm-hmm.

35:30.128 --> 35:32.086
- And that cures
upset stomachs.

35:34.175 --> 35:35.829
- Nettles.
Good for sprains

35:35.872 --> 35:38.179
and insect bites.
- You're so good.

35:38.223 --> 35:40.312
- It's really easy.

35:40.355 --> 35:41.835
♪

35:41.878 --> 35:44.011
You didn't tell me
what this one is.

35:44.054 --> 35:45.360
- Because it's dangerous.

35:45.404 --> 35:47.101
A little bit in a tea
will make you hallucinate

35:47.145 --> 35:49.843
and some more will make you
pass on.

35:49.886 --> 35:53.194
♪

35:53.238 --> 35:54.848
- Um...

35:54.891 --> 35:56.197
That's burdock.
- Mm-hmm.

35:56.241 --> 35:58.678
- It's good for fevers.
- Right.

35:58.721 --> 36:01.028
I love you so much,
you know that?

36:01.071 --> 36:03.204
I love you more than anything
in the whole world.

36:03.248 --> 36:06.425
♪

36:09.863 --> 36:12.126
- Come on!
I'm coming.

36:12.170 --> 36:13.823
Wait!

36:21.440 --> 36:28.490
♪

36:36.846 --> 36:38.892
- We'll see how it goes.

36:40.763 --> 36:42.156
No, no, no.

36:42.200 --> 36:44.114
Hearing's in the morning,
so I'll be back

36:44.158 --> 36:45.855
by the afternoon.

36:45.899 --> 36:47.727
Right.

36:47.770 --> 36:54.821
♪

37:57.144 --> 37:59.059
She was...

37:59.102 --> 38:01.235
sitting on the edge
of the bed.

38:02.845 --> 38:04.978
Was almost naked...

38:05.021 --> 38:06.327
Her nightgown...

38:06.371 --> 38:09.199
had fallen off her shoulder.

38:11.985 --> 38:13.378
- She barely noticed me.

38:13.421 --> 38:16.337
She--she wasn't really
looking at me.

38:17.599 --> 38:20.994
- And how did it feel
seeing your mother like that?

38:25.520 --> 38:28.218
- I didn't know
what was going to happen.

38:30.046 --> 38:31.526
I don't want to do this.

38:31.570 --> 38:34.312
- You're right where
you should be.

38:36.488 --> 38:38.533
You're in the bedroom
looking in on her.

38:41.536 --> 38:44.060
- What did you want
to say to her?

38:46.411 --> 38:48.500
- Stop that.

38:49.414 --> 38:50.850
Stop.

38:54.288 --> 38:56.986
What did she do?

38:58.161 --> 38:59.467
- I don't want to do this
with you.

38:59.511 --> 39:01.077
I don't want to do it.

39:03.253 --> 39:05.386
Is this what you want?

39:05.430 --> 39:09.085
- To hide again and again
and again and again?

39:12.175 --> 39:13.525
What is that feeling
right now?

39:13.568 --> 39:15.527
Tell me.

39:16.049 --> 39:18.530
- I hate you.

39:24.057 --> 39:26.407
- You hate me.

39:26.451 --> 39:28.583
The way you talk.

39:28.627 --> 39:30.977
How do I talk?

39:34.459 --> 39:36.983
- Like you're above it all.

39:38.114 --> 39:41.030
You don't want
to help anyone.

39:41.074 --> 39:42.336
- No.

39:42.380 --> 39:45.426
- You want to control them.

39:45.470 --> 39:47.994
- Yes.

39:48.037 --> 39:50.431
- Like you control your son.

39:51.519 --> 39:53.521
Touching him, smothering him.

39:53.565 --> 39:55.305
Touching him all over--

39:55.349 --> 39:57.090
Julian--my Julian--

39:57.133 --> 39:58.700
as if he's really yours.

39:58.744 --> 40:00.310
- He is mine.
- He isn't.

40:00.354 --> 40:02.356
- He is mine.

40:02.400 --> 40:04.445
- I love him.

40:04.489 --> 40:06.578
I kiss him. I comfort him.

40:06.621 --> 40:08.928
- I know him.

40:08.971 --> 40:10.016
- Mm.

40:13.628 --> 40:16.675
- Your mother couldn't do that
for you, could she?

40:21.680 --> 40:23.986
Never even touched you.

40:24.030 --> 40:29.949
♪

40:29.992 --> 40:31.516
What do you want?

40:31.559 --> 40:33.039
♪

40:35.084 --> 40:36.303
- Say it.
Just say it now.

40:36.346 --> 40:38.000
You'll never say it.
Say it.

40:39.654 --> 40:43.049
♪

40:51.187 --> 40:52.972
♪

40:53.015 --> 40:55.191
Say it.

40:55.235 --> 40:57.193
♪

40:57.237 --> 40:59.239
- Oblivion.

40:59.282 --> 41:06.333
♪

41:09.467 --> 41:16.474
♪

41:34.535 --> 41:37.320
- Julian Walker
is the unwitting product

41:37.364 --> 41:39.148
of a radical upbringing.

41:39.192 --> 41:40.672
His former guardian,
Vera Walker,

41:40.715 --> 41:42.674
admits to having
instructed Julian

41:42.717 --> 41:44.458
about jimsonweed--
the cause of death--

41:44.502 --> 41:47.417
as well as his unorthodox views

41:47.461 --> 41:49.158
on mortality.

41:49.202 --> 41:51.334
He should be rehabilitated,

41:51.378 --> 41:53.075
not incarcerated.

41:53.119 --> 41:56.165
- And how are we to be sure
he won't be a danger again?

41:56.209 --> 41:58.559
- Well, Your Honor, we believe
that this is an issue

41:58.603 --> 42:01.562
of nurture rather than nature.

42:02.607 --> 42:04.478
- Go ahead, Detective.

42:04.522 --> 42:07.263
- Uh, I've gotten
to know Julian

42:07.307 --> 42:10.528
in the course
of the investigation.

42:10.571 --> 42:12.486
He knows what he did

42:12.530 --> 42:15.489
and he knows why he did it.

42:15.533 --> 42:18.361
His first instinct
was to confess.

42:19.493 --> 42:22.191
He had a chance to run away
from all this.

42:22.235 --> 42:25.281
He made a decision
to be here.

42:26.456 --> 42:28.763
Face judgment.

42:30.809 --> 42:32.593
Make amends.

42:36.597 --> 42:39.513
That's more than a lot
of us can say.

42:43.778 --> 42:46.607
- Ms. Farnham,
has DSS chosen a facility

42:46.651 --> 42:49.567
where Julian would be placed
in lieu of prisons?

42:49.610 --> 42:50.611
- Yes, Your Honor.

42:50.655 --> 42:53.614
New Horizons in Syracuse.

42:53.658 --> 42:56.748
- In light of all
extenuating circumstances,

42:56.791 --> 42:59.228
Julian Walker will spend
four years

42:59.272 --> 43:01.143
at New Horizons...

43:01.187 --> 43:02.841
- Subject to review in three.

43:02.884 --> 43:06.148
Court is adjourned.

43:06.192 --> 43:09.412
- Hey.
You did it.

43:09.456 --> 43:12.372
♪

43:12.415 --> 43:14.461
- I'll see you tomorrow.

43:14.504 --> 43:21.555
♪

43:23.688 --> 43:26.168
Thank you.

43:26.212 --> 43:28.867
And thank you for dropping
the charges against me.

43:28.910 --> 43:31.478
I assume that was you.

43:31.521 --> 43:33.785
- Yeah, it was.

43:33.828 --> 43:40.530
♪

43:40.574 --> 43:42.663
- Good-bye.

43:42.707 --> 43:44.491
♪

43:44.534 --> 43:46.667
- Okay.

43:46.711 --> 43:53.718
♪

44:01.203 --> 44:06.687
♪

44:06.731 --> 44:09.385
- You know we have to be back
by 6:00, right?

44:09.429 --> 44:11.431
- I know.

44:11.474 --> 44:13.259
Or we're both in trouble.

44:14.652 --> 44:17.393
Then I have to head home.

44:17.437 --> 44:20.179
- Come on, guys, just tell me
where we're going.

44:20.222 --> 44:22.442
- It's a secret.
- Tell me.

44:22.485 --> 44:29.536
♪

44:38.458 --> 44:45.508
♪

45:03.788 --> 45:05.877
We're really here!

45:05.920 --> 45:12.971
♪

45:26.506 --> 45:31.250
♪

45:31.293 --> 45:33.513
Wow.

45:33.556 --> 45:40.476
♪

45:42.740 --> 45:46.787
♪

45:46.831 --> 45:48.920
My mother would have
liked this.

45:48.963 --> 45:56.014
♪

46:07.852 --> 46:14.859
♪
